cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "RogueGPT: A Controlled Stimulus Generation Framework for News Authenticity Research"
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
type: software
version: "0.1.0"
date-released: "2026-06-13"
license: GPL-3.0-or-later
repository-code: "https://github.com/aloth/RogueGPT"
doi: "10.5281/zenodo.18703138"
url: "https://github.com/aloth/RogueGPT"
abstract: >
  RogueGPT is a controlled stimulus generation framework for AI news authenticity
  research. It provides systematic, reproducible generation of multilingual news
  fragments across multiple large language models, journalistic styles, and content
  formats, together with a MongoDB-backed corpus, a CLI, a Streamlit web interface,
  and a Model Context Protocol (MCP) server for AI agent integration.
